message.content: A Bombus citrinus is a species of bumblebee commonly found in North America. It is easily characterized by its bright yellow color with a black tip on the abdomen. The thorax is also black with yellow stripes. The wings are transparent with a brownish tint. The body has a fuzzy texture, which aids in collecting pollen. Bombus citrinus is an important pollinator for a variety of plants, including tomatoes, blueberries, and strawberries. This bee can be found in a range of habitats, including gardens, meadows, and forests. It is a social insect, living in colonies which can contain several hundred individuals.
